Frank looked at the wolf, still a little confused. The wolf decided to take pity on him. It was his fault the pigs' mom was so paranoid that she hadn't told her kids about the wider world.

"Ok, look, I'll show you. Go pack up - sell anything you can't carry. And don't forget to demolish that depleted uranium house too."

Frank went home and packed up his stuff. He met the wolf on the road, and they headed off to the nearest town. Frank was amazed when they got there. Not by the people, or how wonderful the town was. But by the houses. 

They were terrible. Worse than his eldest brother's original straw house. 

"See, I told you." said the wolf.

And with that Frank's fortune was made. He started up a construction company specializing in houses, and soon he was known as the best builder in the kingdom. 

And that's how Frank became the third richest pig in the world.
